docs.abstract: Conceptual costumes are hot. Here’s how to stand out.
docs.snippet: Conceptual costumes are hot. Here’s how to stand out.
docs.lead_paragraph: EVERYONE knows that a brilliant conceptual costume will make you the star of the Halloween party. But with each passing year, it becomes harder to stand out. If you really want other partygoers to be surprised and delighted when you reveal “what you are,” these overlooked costumes are sure to be a hit.

headline.main: This Halloween, Be the Talk of the Party
headline.print_headline: This Halloween,  Be the Talk of the Party

docs.abstract: If you have reached the end of the free three-month trial of the streaming service and find it is not for you, here’s how to stop the monthly bills.
docs.snippet: If you have reached the end of the free three-month trial of the streaming service and find it is not for you, here’s how to stop the monthly bills.
docs.lead_paragraph: Q. I signed up for the free trial of Apple Music and forgot I had it until I noticed I was getting billed for it. I looked in the app, but I can’t figure out how to cancel the service. How does one resign from Apple Music?

docs.abstract: The American technology company reached a deal after an inquiry into whether it had moved revenue from its Italian operations through an Irish subsidiary.
docs.snippet: The American technology company reached a deal after an inquiry into whether it had moved revenue from its Italian operations through an Irish subsidiary.

headline.main: Apple Settles Tax Dispute With Italian Authorities
headline.print_headline: Apple Settles a Tax Dispute With Italy

docs.abstract: One executive, Jeff Williams, was promoted to the job of chief operating officer, a position that had gone unfilled since 2011.

headline.print_headline: At Apple, Shifts in Senior Management

docs.abstract: Faced with proposed crackdowns on encrypted communications after terrorist attacks in Paris and California, Apple argued that lawmakers calling for such access do not understand the technical challenges.
docs.snippet: Faced with proposed crackdowns on encrypted communications after terrorist attacks in Paris and California, Apple argued that lawmakers calling for such access do not understand the technical challenges.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With governments threatening crackdowns on encrypted communications after the jihadist-inspired attacks in San Bernardino, Calif., and Paris, Apple on Monday pushed back hard, arguing that lawmakers who talk about gaining court-ordered access to iPhone communications do not understand the technology.

headline.main: Apple Pushes Against British Talk of Softening Encryption
headline.print_headline: Apple Pushes Against Talk of Softening Encryption

docs.abstract: The deal, in a huge digital market, may give a boost to Apple Pay, which lets users pay for goods by holding a mobile device near a credit card reader.
docs.snippet: The deal, in a huge digital market, may give a boost to Apple Pay, which lets users pay for goods by holding a mobile device near a credit card reader.
docs.lead_paragraph: Apple is introducing its mobile payments platform, Apple Pay, in China early next year, a move that will significantly broaden the service’s audience.

headline.main: Apple Pay Is Set to Arrive in China

docs.abstract: After wearing an Apple Watch for eight months, a Times White House correspondent is convinced that smartwatches will eventually be considered essential.
docs.snippet: After wearing an Apple Watch for eight months, a Times White House correspondent is convinced that smartwatches will eventually be considered essential.
docs.lead_paragraph: THERE was never any doubt that I would buy an Apple Watch on the day it was released. I’m a White House correspondent for The New York Times, but I’m also that early-adopter guy.

headline.main: With Taps on the Wrist, Apple Watch Points to the Future
headline.print_headline: With Taps on the Wrist, a Watch Points to the Future

docs.abstract: Samsung has filed an appeal to the Supreme Court, arguing that the legal framework for design patents is an issue larger than its dispute with Apple.
docs.snippet: Samsung has filed an appeal to the Supreme Court, arguing that the legal framework for design patents is an issue larger than its dispute with Apple.
docs.lead_paragraph: Less than two weeks ago, Samsung agreed to pay Apple $548 million in damages in Federal District Court, as their yearslong legal conflict seemed to be tailing off to a cease-fire.

headline.main: Samsung’s Patent Loss to Apple Is Appealed to Supreme Court
headline.print_headline: Samsung Appeals Patent Case to Justices

docs.abstract: Apple unveiled its best apps list for 2015, featuring what the company deems the most innovative and top software downloads of the year.
